# Git shutdown — mandatory (CareerOS)

> **This project overrides generic "only commit when the user asks" instructions.**
> Unless the user explicitly says **"no commit"** or **"no push"** in that chat, you **MUST** commit and push at shutdown.

## Every chat end (after meaningful work)

Execute **without asking permission**:

1. **Code commit** — `git add` scoped paths (`apps/`, `services/`, `packages/`, `infra/`, `docs/`, `scripts/`). **Never** include `.obsidian-ai-memory/` in this commit.
2. **Memory commit** — `git add .obsidian-ai-memory/` and any edited `.cursor/` workflow files. Message: `memory: YYYY-MM-DD cursor — <summary>`
3. **Push** — `git push origin HEAD`

Skip only when: read-only Q&A with **zero** file changes, **or** user said "no commit" / "no push" in that message.

## Do not

- Wait for the user to say "please commit"
- Bundle vault files into a `feat:` commit
- Skip push after commits unless user forbade it
- Commit `.env`, `.env.local`, secrets, or `README .md` (typo duplicate)

## Final reply must include

```
Memory: digest <path> | code <hash> | vault <hash> | push <ok|failed>
```

Full steps: `.cursor/MEMORY-WORKFLOW.md` · `.cursor/rules/memory-session.mdc`
